EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to providing public notice of productions.
EventItemMatterName: Providing public notice of productions.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to defeat the Stop Online Piracy Act (“SOPA,” H.R. 3261) and the Preventing Real Online Threats to Economic Creativity and Theft of Intellectual Property Act (“Protect IP Act,” S. 968), which would greatly expand the potential for Internet censorship and place a significant burden on website administrators.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to defeat the Stop Online Piracy Act (“SOPA,” H.R. 3261) and the Preventing Real Online Threats to Economic Creativity and Theft of Intellectual Property Act (“Protect IP Act,” S. 968).

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring radio signal boosting devices in high rise buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring radio signal boosting devices in high rise buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to enforce Chancellor’s Regulation A-801, which requires that students on school buses wear seat belts until the bus comes to a destination stop.
EventItemMatterName: Dept of Education to enforce Chancellor’s Regulation A-801.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to amend the New York City Health and Hospitals Corporation Act to allow private physicians and surgeons in high-risk specialties to purchase professional liability insurance from the Health and Hospitals Corporation (HHC) in exchange for minimal employment with HHC hospitals.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the New York City Health and Hospitals Corporation Act.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution supporting S.1973, the Gun Trafficking Prevention Act of 2012, which would amend the United States Code by creating the crime of trafficking or assisting in the trafficking of  a firearm.
EventItemMatterName: Supporting S.1973, the Gun Trafficking Prevention Act of 2012.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to making the chaining, tying, or attaching of bicycles to street trees illegal.
EventItemMatterName: Making the chaining, tying, or attaching of bicycles to street trees illegal.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting immediate towing of certain vehicles.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting immediate towing of certain vehicles.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution opposing the United State Supreme Court’s interpretation of the Constitution in Citizens United regarding the constitutional rights of corporations, supporting an amendment to the Constitution to provide that corporations are not entitled to the entirety of protections or “rights” of natural persons, specifically so that the expenditure of corporate money to influence the electoral process is no longer a form of constitutionally protected speech, and calling on Congress to begin the process of amending the Constitution.
EventItemMatterName: Opposing the US Supreme Court’s interpretation of the Constitution in Citizens United.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Waterfronts
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to discharges in certain designated bodies of water.
EventItemMatterName: Discharges in certain designated bodies of water.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to authorizing an increase in the amount to be expended in six business improvement districts.
EventItemMatterName: Authorizing an increase in the amount to be expended in six business improvement districts.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to decreasing the number of vehicles required to qualify for base station license.
EventItemMatterName: Decreasing the number of vehicles required to qualify for base station license.

EventItemMatterName: Approving the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Expense Budget.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution concerning the increase in the annual expenditure for the 34th Street, the Grand Central,  the 125th Street, the Mosholu-Jerome-East Gun Hill Road, the Fordham Road and the Bayside Village  Business Improvement Districts, and the setting of the date, time and place for the hearing of the local law increasing the annual expenditure for such districts.
EventItemMatterName: Increase annual expediture of six BIDs.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to noise levels in commercial and manufacturing districts.
EventItemMatterName: Noise levels in commercial and manufacturing districts.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Mental Retardation, Alcoholism, Drug Abuse and Disability Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring that agencies educate business owners on issues concerning access for persons with disabilities.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring that agencies educate business owners on issues concerning access for persons with disabilities.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York City Congressional Delegation to vote to disapprove H.R. 3630 which cuts federal unemployment benefits for long term unemployment and instead to support full renewal of the federal unemployment insurance program through 2012.
EventItemMatterName: NYC Congressional Delegation to vote to disapprove H.R. 3630 which cuts federal unemployment benefits for long term unemployment.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of transportation to post on its website pedestrian related project information accessible to people with disabilities.
